description:
Omi Remalante Jr began his comic book career on July 2008 with Capestone Connection, TX where he was the colorist of Borderwall. He made several independent books before landing the job of colorist for Majestic XII by Justin Leach.

Past works include OZ / Wonderland Chronicles, Grimm Fairy Tales # 80, Robyn Hood # 4, Liberator ending credits artworks to name a few.
name: Omi Remalante Jr

deck: A comic book artist who has recently begun to provide covers for Marvel.

Born in the Philippines, now lives in Toronto, Ontario, Canada.

Mostly known for covers.

He also had work featured at the Labyrinth and the Comic Book Lounge in Toronto.

description: Los Angeles born and Midwest raised, B. Alex Thompson is a comic book writer, screenwriter, letterer, and artist who has done work for Alias Enterprises, Approbation Comics, Arcana Studios, Lion Forge Comics, and Graphic Planet. Thompson is mostly known for his humor/horror title Chaos Campus: Sorority Girls vs. Zombies which has over twenty-five issues released with more in the works.
